					<head>Targum on Chronicles</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79150252" rend="visible">
						<summary>Targum on Chronicles, provided with vowel-points.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="tmr">Aramaic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79150252">
							<title xml:lang="en">Divre ha-yamim </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">דברי הימים</title>
							<locus from="2r" to="62r"/>
							<note>
								<p>Contains original pagination in Arabic numerals. </p>
								<p>Copied in 1660 from a manuscript in the University of Cambridge which was dated 1347. </p>
								<p>Has two colophons, of the scribe of the original manuscript and of the copyist. </p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">חזק ונתחזק חיים הסופר לא ירזק [!] סיימתי הכתובים עם התרגום <date when="1660" calendar="Hebrew">בשנת חמשת אלפים ומאה ושבע לבריאות [!] עולם בששי בשבת באחד ועשרים יום לחדש טבת</date>. <locus n="62r"/>
							</colophon>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="2r" to="29v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">1Chronicles</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="29v" to="62r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">2Chronicles</title>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>62 folio<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>210</height>
										<width>160</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>183</height>
										<width>115</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>62 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
									<p>Original Latin pagination. </p>
								</foliation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="30 32" writtenLines="30 32">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Square script, punctuated, of the 17th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Thomas Carston</name>, copyist of this manuscript, inscibed with his name in the colophon, with a date of <date calendar="Gregorian">1660</date>: folio 62r. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 1r: owner's note: <q>Sum Jois Covel ex dono Mri. Dom. Duckfield. M. Charissimi viri. maij 9 1702.</q> </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600, Harleian binding of brown leather.</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
